        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <hi rend="underline">Hebrew</hi>
            </p>
            <p>To my friend, etc, <addressee>Rev. Leeser</addressee>:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I, too, request that you grant the wish of<lb/> my dear friend,
                    <persName>Finkelstein</persName>, which is also my<lb/> wish. Don't let it
                surprise you that I haven't<lb/> written to you for <del>some</del> long, as is
                proper between two<lb/> good friends. The reason is that I had no peace<lb/> from a
                man who hates me and who is my bitter<lb/> enemy, <persName>Zoi</persName>, a scribe
                from <placeName>New York</placeName>, who came here<lb/> last winter and accused me
                of very ugly doings<lb/> in <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> He went from house to house
                slaughter-<lb/>ing fowl, and, with a smooth tongue, he aroused<lb/> the entire
                community against me. A long time<lb/> posted until his lies <del>it became
                    known</del> were refuted<lb/> from <placeName>New York</placeName>, and all the
                honor I received<lb/> there became known. Then the dispute quieted<lb/> down, but
                two enemies remained, and,<lb/> after the <date>Passover</date>, when he departed, I
                began<lb/> to open my eyes. But now recently, the two<lb/> enemies once more aroused
                themselves, <del>an</del><lb/> since this man is coming here. For myself, I<lb/>
                have always loved peace and have always kept<lb/> away from dispute. Therefore, I
                ask with<lb/> my very soul that you be good enough to</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>announce in your newspaper to all the<lb/> Jews that there is a certain man, a
                rabbi<lb/> a chazan and a schochet, a reader of the<lb/> Torah, a Mohel, and a
                shofar blower, and<lb/> my view is that you should not reveal my<lb/> name, for, as
                the saying goes, "One should not<lb/> throw away muddy water, unless he has<lb/>
                clean water," and for a wise man like you,<lb/> this List is sufficient. I am
                waiting<lb/> expectantly for your reply. Whatever the<lb/> cost of the printing will
                be, please let me<lb/> know and I will pay <del>whatever</del> as well as I<lb/>
                can. I also have shofars (<add>?</add>)<lb/> to sell which I am having made by a
                skilled workman,<lb/><persName> Moses Katzenellenbogen</persName>.</p>
            <p><persName role="author">Moses Bogen</persName>.</p>
